<br>
You're not considering the whole picture if you don't think there will be a market for researched spells. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The whole picture is = 90%<br>
<br>
Yes, there are those FEW spells that would make this worthwhile for a week or 2.  Within a month, I bet you constantly see 20-30 Malo's in the bazaar for 10K a pop and not selling.  Within 4 months Malo will be down to under 1K.<br>
<br>
The math in short, lets say there are 10k shammies on 10 servers that need Malo.  Thats 1K shammy per server.  If 10 Malo's enter the server each day (which won't be too outrageous of a number) through reasearch, then in 10 days you've taken care of 10% of the demand.  In the first month, 30% of the demand would have been nulified.  The remaining 700 shammies per server that need/want malo, don't have it either because they didn't have the pp to buy it or weren't in the bazaar at the right times.<br>
<br>
Since supply was higher than normal the price dropped, since a good deal of the demand has been met the price will drop even further.  With those numbers, 3 1/3 months would see the end of the immediate demand, then the demand is wayyy below supply.  So your a shammy and you want Malo, do you buy it today for 80K, do you wait 2 weeks til it's 40K, do you wait a month til it's 10K, or do you wait 4 months til the market is flooded and pick up your copy for 1k or less?<br>
<br>
A shammy would be blind to buy Malo today, or even in the next few weeks.<br>
<br>
It's probably a stretch to say there would be 1k shammies on any given server that needs/wants Malo, it's also a stretch to think that a guilded 60 shammy will have to buy Malo, since the guild would benefit more from pharming the research drops and handing those to an int caster to hit combine, thus filling that guilds need for the spell.  All that with no pp changing hands.  Taking the guilded 60+ shammies that need Malo out of the picture, how many unguilded 60+ shammies would be left in the market to buy Malo?  Less than 50 I'd bet.<br>
<br>
The state teaches me to look at 90%, leave the 10% outlyers to the side (i.e. the spell Malo would be part of the ignored 10%).  When you look at the 10% thats ignored you can see why it should have been ignored.  It does no good to calculate sales for Malo, when 99% of the shammies that need it will get it w/o paying (through guild involvement).  The 90% that guilds wouldn't bother pharming drops for, is what needs to be looked at.  These spells are 5pp in the bazaar ATM, this is why guilds wouldn't bother pharming for them.<br>
<br>
It may sound like I am talking circles, but any spell above 1kpp, guilds will pharm the research components for (as opposed to buying).  The remaining spells are already dirt cheap. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1810<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 9:55:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=571.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: grr</span><hr size=1> So basically you're upset because your new &quot;job&quot; (hitting combine) won't equal huge amounts of cash in your pocket?<br>
